A and the Study of Animal Domestication|journal=Annual Review of Animal Biosciences|volume=5|year=2016|last1=Machugh|first1=David E.|last2=Larson|first2=Greger|last3=Orlando|first3=Ludovic|pmid=27813680|pages=329\u2013351|url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/82ed8640f90b5523b7091abf77898ebeb92c6a2c}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=malmstrom2008>{{cite journal|doi=10.1186/1471-2148-8-71|pmid=18307773|pmc=2288593|title=Barking up the wrong tree: Modern northern European dogs fail to explain their origin|journal=BMC Evolutionary Biology|volume=8|pages=71|year=2008|last1=Malmstr\u00f6m|first1=Helena|last2=Vil\u00e0|first2=Carles|last3=Gilbert|first3=M|last4=Stor\u00e5|first4=Jan|last5=Willerslev|first5=Eske|last6=Holmlund| first6=Gunilla|last7=G\u00f6therstr\u00f6m|first7=Anders}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=maher2011>{{cite journal|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0015815|pmid=21298094|pmc=3027631|title=A Unique Human-Fox Burial from a Pre-Natufian Cemetery in the Levant (Jordan)|journal=PLoS ONE|volume=6|issue=1|pages=e15815|year=2011|last1=Maher|first1=Lisa A|last2=Stock|first2=Jay|last3=Finney|first3=Sarah|last4=Heywood|first4=James J. N|last5=Miracle|first5=Preston T|last6=Banning|first6=Edward B}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=morey1992>{{cite journal | author = Morey Darcy F | year = 1992 | title = Size, shape, and development in the evolution of the domestic dog | url = | journal = Journal of Archaeological Science | volume = 19 | issue = 2| pages = 181\u2013204 | doi=10.1016/0305-4403(92)90049-9}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=morey1994>{{cite journal|last1=Morey|first1=D.|title=The Early Evolution of the Domestic Dog|journal=American Scientist|publisher=Sigma Xi, The Scientific Research Society|volume=82|issue=4|year=1994|pages=336\u2013347|jstor=29775234}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=morey2010>{{cite book|last1=Morey|first1=D.|title=Dogs: Domestication and the Development of a Social Bond|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=2010|chapter=Ch.3|pages=55\u201356|isbn=9780521757430|chapter-url={{Google books|plainur