ene wolf variation|journal=Journal of Archaeological Science|volume=68|pages=1\u20134|year=2016|last1=Perri|first1=Angela}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=perri2019>{{cite journal|doi=10.1017/aaq.2018.74|title=New Evidence of the Earliest Domestic Dogs in the Americas|journal=American Antiquity|volume=84|pages=68\u201387|year=2019|last1=Perri|first1=Angela|last2=Widga|first2=Chris|last3=Lawler|first3=Dennis|last4=Martin|first4=Terrance|last5=Loebel|first5=Thomas|last6=Farnsworth|first6=Kenneth|last7=Kohn|first7=Luci|last8=Buenger|first8=Brent|doi-access=free}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=pidoplichko1969>Pidoplichko, I. G. (1969) Late Palaeolithic dwellings of Mammoth bones in the Ukraine. Academy of Sciences of the Ukraine. Institute of Zoology. Nauka, Doumka, Kiev. (in Russian)</ref>\n\n<ref name=pidoplichko1998>Pidoplichko I.G. (1998) Upper Paleolithic Dwellings of Mammoth Bones in the Ukraine. Oxford: BAR International Series 712</ref>\n\n<ref name=pilot2006>{{cite journal|doi=10.1111/j.1365-294X.2006.03110.x|pmid=17107481|title=Ecological factors influence population genetic structure of European grey wolves|journal=Molecular Ecology|volume=15|issue=14|pages=4533\u201353|year=2006|last1=Pilot|first1=Malgorzata|last2=Jedrzejewski|first2=Wlodzimierz|last3=Branicki|first3=Wojciech|last4=Sidorovich|first4=Vadim E.|last5=Jedrzejewska|first5=Bogumila|last6=Stachura|first6=Krystyna|last7=Funk|first7=Stephan M.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=pierotti2017p83>{{Harvnb|Pierotti|Fogg|2017|pp=83\u201393}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=pierotti2017p101>{{Harvnb|Pierotti|Fogg|2017|pp=101}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=pionnier2011>{{cite journal | last1 = Pionnier-Capitan | first1 = M |display-authors=etal  | year = 2011 | title = New evidence for Upper Palaeolithic small domestic dogs in South-Western Europe | url = | journal = J. Archaeol. Sci. | volume = 38 | issue = 9| pages = 2123\u20132140 | doi=10.1016/j.jas.2011.02.028}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Prassack2020>{{cite journal|doi=10.1016/j.jas.2020.105092|title=Dental microwear 